Name: bronchus mucoepidermoid carcinoma
Definition: A bronchus cancer that has_material_basis_in squamous cells

Name: trachea mucoepidermoid carcinoma
Definition: A trachea carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of squamous cells

Name: thymus mucoepidermoid carcinoma
Definition: A corneal disease that is characterized by inflammation of the cornea.

Name: lacrimal gland mucoepidermoid carcinoma
Definition: A breast carcinoma that represents a mixed group of malignant neoplasms characterized by the histologic presence of two or more cellular types.

Name: laryngeal mucoepidermoid carcinoma
Definition: A thyroid gland carcinoma that is composed of groups of squamoid and mucous cells
